<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Elemental Empathy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <br>
Slot Description <br>
3:  Increase STR by 60 <br>
4:  Increase Attack Speed by 60% <br>
6:  Increase AC by 18 <br>
  <br>
Mana: 300 Skill: Alteration <br>
Casting Time: 6 Recast Time: 12 <br>
Fizzle Time: 2.5 Range: 100 <br>
Short Buff Box: No Target Type: Pet <br>
Spell Type: Beneficial Source: Live 01/09 <br>
Classes: MAG/52 <br>
Duration: 1 hour(s) 30.0 mins <br>
Autocast: <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Stoicism</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Cast on other: Someone glows with energy.<br>
<br>
Anyone know what &quot;Autocast&quot; means? Interestingly, the autocast on this new spell is...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Stoicism</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Slot Description <br>
1:  Increase Hitpoints v2 by 160 per tick <br>
3:  Decrease Movement by 100% <br>
11:  Decrease Attack Speed by 30% <br>
<br>
Mana: 180 Skill: Alteration <br>
Casting Time: 6 Recast Time: 0 <br>
Fizzle Time: 2.5 Range: 100 <br>
Short Buff Box: No Target Type: Single <br>
Spell Type: Beneficial Source: Live 01/09 <br>
Classes: SHM/44 <br>
Duration: 4 ticks <br>
Cast on you: You fall into a state of stoicism. <br>
Cast on other: Someone falls into a state of stoicism.<br>
<br>
Anyone have any thoughts? Personally, my guess is that it would add this &quot;spell&quot; to the pet's spell line up, so whatever pet that has this pet buff would &quot;autocast&quot; this along with it's other spells. In short, Elemental Empathy on Earth pet would mean that asides from the root that it casts, he would also cast this in addition or in place of root. Of course this is just speculation.<br>
<br>
*Edit* Upon rereading the effect and seeing that it's a new Shaman spell with the &quot;heal&quot; icon and is flagged a beneficial spell, I guess it could also be a heal in the Shaman's Torpor line which your pet would cast on you. However, if that were the case, I'm less than enthusiastic, since an uncontrollable heal that also &quot;roots&quot; you is not necessarily a good thing.<br>
<br>
